OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThe blind Ukrainian amputee
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fwhose wife's voice kept him
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Falive                      
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, As Serhiy slowly began to regain       
OL,6, consciousness in his hospital bed in   
OL,7, Kyiv, he realised he couldn't see,     
OL,8, speak, or feel his legs - but he could 
OL,9, hear his wife Valeria's voice.         
OL,10, Comforted, he lost consciousness again.
OL,12,FIt was a pattern that lasted weeks. The
OL,13,Fseverely injured Ukrainian soldier     
OL,14,Fwould wake up to darkness and panic,   
OL,15,Funable to communicate because of the   
OL,16,Ftube down his throat - but every time  
OL,17,Fhe heard Valeria, he settled down.     
OL,19,F"That's what kept me fighting," he     
OL,20,Ftells the BBC's Ukrainecast podcast.   
